t: Psalm 94
O*p Lord*s God, to whom vengeance belongeth; O God, to whom vengeance belongeth, shew thyself.
Lift*p up thyself, thou judge of the earth: render a reward to the proud.
Lord,*sp how long shall the wicked, how long shall the wicked triumph?
How*p long shall they utter and speak hard things? and all the workers of iniquity boast themselves?
They*p break in pieces thy people, O Lord,*s and afflict thine heritage.
They*p slay the widow and the stranger, and murder the fatherless.
Yet*p they say, The Lord*s shall not see, neither shall the God of Jacob regard it.
Understand,*p ye brutish among the people: and ye fools, when will ye be wise?
He*p that planted the ear, shall he not hear? he that formed the eye, shall he not see?
He*p that chastiseth the heathen, shall not he correct? he that teacheth man knowledge, shall not he know?
The*p Lord*s knoweth the thoughts of man, that they are vanity.
Blessed*p is the man whom thou chastenest, O Lord,*s and teachest him out of thy law;
That*p thou mayest give him rest from the days of adversity, until the pit be digged for the wicked.
For*p the Lord*s will not cast off his people, neither will he forsake his inheritance.
But*p judgment shall return unto righteousness: and all the upright in heart shall follow it.
Who*p will rise up for me against the evildoers? or who will stand up for me against the workers of iniquity?
Unless*p the Lord*s had been my help, my soul had almost dwelt in silence.
When*p I said, My foot slippeth; thy mercy, O Lord,*s held me up.
In*p the multitude of my thoughts within me thy comforts delight my soul.
Shall*p the throne of iniquity have fellowship with thee, which frameth mischief by a law?
They*p gather themselves together against the soul of the righteous, and condemn the innocent blood.
But*p the Lord*s is my defence; and my God is the rock of my refuge.
And*p he shall bring upon them their own iniquity, and shall cut them off in their own wickedness; yea, the Lord*s our God shall cut them off.
